---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import SectionWrapper from '../components/SectionWrapper.astro';
import VideoBackground from '../components/VideoBackground.astro';
---

<Layout title="FAQ" description="Frequently asked questions about chiropractic care at The Bridge Chiropractic. Learn about first visits, treatment approaches, insurance, and more.">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="hero-fullbleed" style="background: var(--color-primary);">
    <div class="hero-fullbleed__content">
      <h1 class="hero-fullbleed__title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
      <p class="hero-fullbleed__subtitle">Everything you need to know about chiropractic care, what to expect, and how we can help.</p>
      <div class="hero-fullbleed__cta">
        <a href="#" class="btn btn--white btn--lg" data-cal-link="sdbridgechiropractic/30min" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}'>Book Your Visit</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <SectionWrapper spacing="normal">
    <div class="faq-section" data-animate="fade-up">
      <div class="faq-section__header">
        <span class="faq-section__label">Common Questions</span>
        <h2 class="faq-section__title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-grid">
        <div class="faq-column">
          <details class="faq-item" data-animate="fade-up">
            <summary class="faq-summary">
              What should I expect on my first visit?
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" class="faq-icon"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              Your first visit is about clarity, not pressure. We'll discuss your concerns, perform a detailed movement and mobility assessment, and determine what's contributing to your symptoms. If care is appropriate, adjustments are precise and controlled, tailored to your comfort and response. You'll leave with a clear understanding of what's going on and what the next steps look like, so you can make an informed decision.
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item" data-animate="fade-up">
            <summary class="faq-summary">
              Do adjustments hurt?
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" class="faq-icon"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              Most adjustments are not painful. Some areas may feel tender if they're already irritated, but care is delivered in a controlled, precise way. The goal is to reduce discomfort, not create it. If something doesn't feel right, we adjust the approach.
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item" data-animate="fade-up">
            <summary class="faq-summary">
              Do I have to be "cracked" to get results?
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" class="faq-icon"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              No. Effective care is about precision and matching the approach to your body. Some techniques involve a joint release (audible noise), while others are gentle and low force. The goal isn't the noise, but aligning the spine to increase mobility and decrease pain. Your comfort and response guide the technique used.
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item" data-animate="fade-up">
            <summary class="faq-summary">
              How many visits will I need?
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" class="faq-icon"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              That depends on your goals, the severity of the issue, and how your body responds. Some people improve quickly, while others benefit from a short structured plan to stabilize progress. You will receive clear recommendations and options so you can decide what feels right for you.
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-column">
          <details class="faq-item" data-animate="fade-up">
            <summary class="faq-summary">
              Do you accept insurance?
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" class="faq-icon"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              We are an out-of-network provider for most insurance plans. Many policies include out-of-network benefits that may reimburse a portion of your care. We verify your benefits and submit claims on your behalf when applicable so the process is straightforward. For patients with traditional Medicare, covered services are billed directly and Medicare typically pays a portion of the visit, which helps make care more affordable. Our team will review your specific benefits and explain what to expect before you begin.
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item" data-animate="fade-up">
            <summary class="faq-summary">
              What makes your approach different?
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" class="faq-icon"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              Care is tailored to how your body responds. Instead of using a single technique for everyone, adjustments, soft tissue therapy, and movement training are combined when appropriate to improve results. If something is not progressing as expected, the plan is reassessed and refined. The focus is long-term function, not just temporary relief.
            </div>
          </details>

          <details class="faq-item" data-animate="fade-up">
            <summary class="faq-summary">
              Can chiropractic help if I have arthritis?
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" class="faq-icon"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg>
            </summary>
            <div class="faq-content">
              Chiropractic cannot reverse arthritis, but it can improve joint mobility, reduce stiffness, and support surrounding muscles. Many patients with arthritis feel better when movement improves and irritation decreases. The goal is to help you stay active and maintain function safely.
            </div>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </SectionWrapper>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <VideoBackground
    videoUrl="https://res.cloudinary.com/dku1gnuat/video/upload/v1772139027/fitness-exercise-and-running-woman-at-beach-for-2025-12-17-11-33-16-utc_htkq3f.mov"
    posterImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1571019614242-c5c5dee9f50b?w=1920&h=1080&fit=crop"
    overlayOpacity={0.7}
    class="cta-premium"
  >
    <div class="container container-narrow" data-animate="fade-up">
      <h2>Still Have Questions?</h2>
      <p>We're happy to answer any questions about our practice, your condition, or whether chiropractic care might be right for you.</p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 16px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--white btn--lg">Contact Us</a>
        <a href="tel:8582777500" class="btn btn--secondary btn--lg" style="background: transparent; border: 2px solid white; color: white;">Call (858) 277-7500</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </VideoBackground>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero-fullbleed--static .hero-fullbleed__image {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    z-index: 0;
  }

  /* FAQ Sections */
  .faq-section {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .faq-section__header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  .faq-section__label {
    display: inline-block;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .faq-section__title {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* FAQ Grid Layout */
  .faq-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    gap: var(--space-2xl);
  }

  .faq-column {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .faq-item:first-child {
    border-top: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  }

  .faq-summary {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-lg);
    padding: 22px 0;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1.0625rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-charcoal);
    cursor: pointer;
    list-style: none;
    transition: color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-summary::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-summary::marker {
    display: none;
    content: '';
  }

  .faq-summary:hover {
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }

  .faq-icon {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease;
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  details[open] .faq-icon {
    transform: rotate(180deg);
  }

  .faq-content {
    padding-bottom: 22px;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--color-gray-dark);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
  }

  /* Responsive */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .faq-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0;
    }

    .faq-section__title {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .faq-summary {
      padding: 18px 0;
      font-size: 1rem;
      gap: var(--space-md);
    }

    .faq-content {
      padding-bottom: 18px;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 480px) {
    .faq-section__title {
      font-size: 1.375rem;
    }

    .faq-summary {
      font-size: 0.9375rem;
    }

    .faq-content {
      font-size: 0.875rem;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  // Scroll-triggered animations
  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    entries.forEach(entry => {
      if (entry.isIntersecting) {
        entry.target.classList.add('animated');
        observer.unobserve(entry.target);
      }
    });
  }, { root: null, rootMargin: '-100px', threshold: 0.1 });

  document.querySelectorAll('[data-animate]').forEach(el => observer.observe(el));
</script>
